cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on word and sentence representations. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to improve the learned representations, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a gating mechanism, which is a common technique in neural networks, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category. The paper also mentions the use of character-level representations, which is a common technique in text recognition and computer vision, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the learned representations in downstream tasks, which is a common topic in neural networks and optimization, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category.
